CITY COURT OF NEW YORK

—GENERAL TERM,

MAY, 1895. The Edison General Electric Co., Respondent, v. Sylvester H. Kneeland, Appellant. Appeal from a judgment in favor of plaintiff. A. Prentice, for appellant. Charles 0. Brewster, for respondent. Per Curiam.

Judgment appealed from affirmed, with costs.

Present: Newbubger, Oonlan and Fitzsimons, JJ.

Judgment affirmed, with costs.
